missrecipe = '[{"name" : "pizza", "origin" : "Italian", "photo" : "https://images.pexels.com/photos/208537/pexels-photo-208537.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&dpr=2&h=650&w=940", "ingredient1" : "Warm water 600 mL", "ingredient2" : "Flour type00 1000g", "ingredient3" : "Package of active dry yeast", "ingredient4" : "Extra virgin olive oil 2 tbsp", "ingredient5" : "Salt 2 tbsp", "ingredient6" : "Sugar 1 tbsp", "ingredient7" : "", "ingredient8" : "", "ingredient9" : "", "ingredient10" : "", "instruction" : "Put the sifted flour in a bowl and add the crumbled brewer yeast and mix the use of a wooden spoon. We pour the image in several stages, continuing to mix so that it will be absorbed by the flour. Add the salt and pour the extra virgin olive oil while continuing to stir. This type of dough, mixed raw is called no knead. We cover the bowl with a sheet of cling film and let it rise for 30 minutes at room temperature. The ideal is to put it in the oven with the oven off mode so as to have a constant temperature of 26-28 °. If you do not have this feature you can wrap the bowl in a blanket and leave it in a place sheltered from currents. After this time, we transfer the dough to the work surface and fold it back on itself repeating the operation on all 4 sides. Then three times, we close the dough by pulling it with our hands towards us. Do not worry if initially the consistency will be rather sticky. Put the dough back in the bowl, cover with plastic wrap and let rise for another 20 minutes. We repeat this step two more times; the last time, before putting the dough back in the bowl, pour a little oil and finally let it rise at room temperature for at 3 hours"},{"name" : "sushi", "origin" : "Japan", "photo" : "https://cdn.pixabay.com/photo/2014/06/21/02/29/sushi-373588_960_720.jpg", "ingredient1" : "Sushi rice 500 g", "ingredient2" : "Sugar 60 g", "ingredient3" : "Water 600 ml", "ingredient4" : "Rice vinegar 150 ml", "ingredient5" : "Salt 5 g", "ingredient6" : "Seaweed kombu 1", "ingredient7" : "Salmon fillet 1", "ingredient8" : "Soy sauce", "ingredient9" : "", "ingredient10" : "", "instruction" : "Pour vinegar, sugar and salt into a saucepan; Heat gently until salt and sugar have melted, do not heat too much or boil vinegar. Let it cool and if you wish, leave the kombu seaweed to soak for 48 hours. The first step is to wash the rice, to do this it is necessary to gently massage it in a little water for a few minutes, taking care to change the water several times until the latter remains clear; After washing leave the rice to soak in water for 15/20 minutes, this step can be skipped if cooking is prolonged. However, the soaking phase is strongly recommended to ensure rapid and uniform cooking, especially if a lot of rice is prepared. Put the rice and water in a saucepan. Bring to the boil in the shortest time possible with an uncovered pot, at the boil, set the stove to minimum and cover the pot. Cook for 10/12 minutes. Turn off the heat and leave the rice in the pan for 10/15 minutes without removing the lid. Pour the rice and place it in a mound shape, preferably in a low wooden container (Hangiri). Pour all the seasoning and gently separate the rice without crushing the beans. Once the rice and the vinegar have been mixed, let it rest for a few minutes, covering with a damp cloth, so that the rice does not dry. Then use the warm rice to prepare the sushi. Do not let the rice cool down too much, the right temperature is body temperature, or at least not below 25/30 ° C. Wet your hands in warm water, take some rice and make some meatballs by pressing, but not too much, so that it does not come apart. At this point take a slice of fish and place it on the meatball, pressing lightly so as to make it one with the rice; if you like spicy you can put a little wasabi inside. Repeat the process until all the slices of fish are used. Place the nigiri on the platter and camp them with a ball of wasabi, a few slices of ginger and of course the soy sauce in a small bowl." }]';







